Any tobacco product manufacturer that sells cigarettes to consumers within the State, whether directly or through a distributor, retailer, or similar intermediary or intermediaries, after June 1, 1999, shall either:
become a participating manufacturer, as that term is defined in section II(jj) of the Master Settlement Agreement, and generally perform its financial obligations under the Master Settlement Agreement; or
place into a qualified escrow fund by April 15 of the year following the year in question the following amounts, as such amounts are adjusted for inflation:
for 1999, $.0094241 per unit sold after June 1, 1999;
for 2000, $.0104712 per unit sold;
for each of 2001 and 2002, $.0136125 per unit sold;
for each of 2003, 2004, 2005, and 2006, $.0167539 per unit sold; and
for 2007 and each year thereafter, $.0188482 per unit sold.
